ated_at":"2013-10-08t08:47:32z","updated_at":"2013-10-08t08:47:32z","body":"just saw this in the console:\r\n{\"app\":\"webdav client\",\"message\":\"method not allowed\",\"level\":3,\"time\":\"2013-10-08t08:44:19+00:00\"}\r\n\r\nit seems it's thrown in the filetype() method in webdav.php.\r\nsince this method fails it's not possible to distinguish files from dirs."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/25873711","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/4923#issuecomment-25873711","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/4923","id":25873711,"user":{"login":"pvince81","id":277525,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f89d7c394e6dcdf87a91c75ac3b2ccbe8.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe","url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81","html_url":"https://github.com/pvince81","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-08t08:51:11z","updated_at":"2013-10-08t08:51:11z","body":"this is when calling propfind() on the webdav client lib.\r\ni suspect that the target server for the mount (which runs oc5) doesn't support propfind.\r\neither we need to use another method (or fallback to another method) or make oc5 use propfind.\r\n\r\ni'll have a try against oc6."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/25875903","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/4923#issuecomment-25875903","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/4923","id":25875903,"user":{"login":"pvince81","id":277525,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f89d7c394e6dcdf87a91c75ac3b2ccbe8.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe","url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81","html_url":"https://github.com/pvince81","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-08t09:29:45z","updated_at":"2013-10-08t09:29:45z","body":"the \"method not allowed\" error also appears when mounting an oc6 dir through webdav."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/25880281","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/4923#issuecomment-25880281","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/4923","id":25880281,"user":{"login":"pvince81","id":277525,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f89d7c394e6dcdf87a91c75ac3b2ccbe8.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe","url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81","html_url":"https://github.com/pvince81","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-08t10:51:35z","updated_at":"2013-10-08t10:51:35z","body":"it looks like webdav access on owncloud is possible through two url formats:\r\n1) http://host/owncloud\r\n2) http://host/owncloud/files/webdav.php/\r\n\r\nso far i've always tested with 1). it seems to be able to download the file list, but the \"method not allowed\" error is thrown. files can't be downloaded\r\n\r\nfor 2), the files are scanned properly, thumbnails appear and i can download files.\r\n\r\nso this means that the webdav proxy/rerouting from case 1) somehow doesn't allow the propfind method to be called. it could be a htaccess setting as well. needs further investigation.\r\n\r\nit seems that the ajax navigation itself is a bit broken as well as i needed to refresh the page to make it work. i'll address this as a separate issue."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/25880880","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/4923#issuecomment-25880880","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/4923","id":25880880,"user":{"login":"pvince81","id":277525,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f89d7c394e6dcdf87a91c75ac3b2ccbe8.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe","url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81","html_url":"https://github.com/pvince81","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-08t11:03:22z","updated_at":"2013-10-08t11:03:22z","body":"found another hint in the access logs of the target server.\r\nwhen reading the file list, this comes out:\r\n127.0.0.1 - - [08/oct/2013:12:57:53 +0200] \"propfind /owncloud2/ http/1.1\" 302 - \"-\" \"-\"\r\n127.0.0.1 - - [08/oct/2013:12:57:53 +0200] \"propfind /owncloud2/remote.php/webdav/ http/1.1\" 401 291 \"-\" \"-\"\r\n127.0.0.1 - root [08/oct/2013:12:57:53 +0200] \"propfind /owncloud2/remote.php/webdav/ http/1.1\" 207 532 \"-\" \"-\"\r\n\r\nthe client is auto-redirected to the correct path by the code in base.php:686\r\n\r\nbut then when trying to download a picture, it tries to access the following:\r\n127.0.0.1 - - [08/oct/2013:12:58:08 +0200] \"propfind /owncloud2/p1060368.jpg http/1.1\" 405 973 \"-\" \"-\"\r\n\r\nwhich is itself not handled by index.php -> base.php.\r\n\r\ni'm not sure whether we can officially support this url scheme as there might be path names. for example \"/owncloud2/subdir\" where subdir could match one of another app's path.\r\n\r\none idea would be to split \"owncloud / webdav\" to \"owncloud\" and \"webdav\" and have the \"owncloud\" backend be clever and auto-add \"remove.php/webdav\" when making requests. this is to prevent user errors where they'd see that it's an \"owncloud\" connection and only input the root of the owncloud server instead of the full path.\r\n\r\nwhat do you think @karlitschek @deepdiver1975 @icewind1991 ?\r\nis it possible to detect that the webdav target is owncloud ?"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/25881918","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/4923#issuecomment-25881918","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/4923","id":25881918,"user":{"login":"deepdiver1975","id":1005065,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/bdba071ed68da9ce8edae53c364902ef?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f67e101ad9531b7d25697b76e503e062e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"bdba071ed68da9ce8edae53c364902ef","url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975","html_url":"https://github.com/deepdiver1975","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-08t11:24:37z","updated_at":"2013-10-08t11:24:37z","body":"the official webdav url includes remove.php/webdav and this is printed in the personal settings as well as the documentation.\r\nfrom my point of view this should be enough.\r\n\r\nin case you want to detect if you are talking to another owncloud instance you should get status.php\r\nyou will get back a json containing version information etc.\r\n\r\nbtw: this is how the clie